    {
      "id": "PopularPost220712",
      "post_content": "@NARFNra: Simply put, the original [Mirrorweave](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Mirrorweave) (targeting [Ink-Treader Nephilim](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Ink-Treader Nephilim)) is the last one to resolve, so everything will be a copy of the last creature targeted (because its copy will be the first to resolve).  \n  \n@okfs87\\_7: If the last creature targeted is another [Ink-Treader Nephilim](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Ink-Treader Nephilim), it's not that big of a deal. Since only spells that are *cast* are copied by its ability, it won't further copy those copies. Otherwise, any single-target spell would cause an infinite loop with just a [Clone](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Clone).  \n  \n@ratrase & OneFishTwoFish: [Groundbreaker](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Groundbreaker) is very similar to both [Force of Savagery](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Force of Savagery) and [Ball Lightning](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Ball Lightning), and I'd wager that it's easier to generate ![2](/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&name=2&type=symbol)![White or Blue](/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&name=WU&type=symbol)![White or Blue](/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&name=WU&type=symbol)![Green](/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&name=G&type=symbol)![Green](/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&name=G&type=symbol)![Green](/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&name=G&type=symbol) than either ![2](/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&name=2&type=symbol)![White or Blue](/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&name=WU&type=symbol)![White or Blue](/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&name=WU&type=symbol)![Red](/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&name=R&type=symbol)![Red](/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&name=R&type=symbol)![Red](/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&name=R&type=symbol) or all the cards required to make the [Force of Savagery](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Force of Savagery) combo work. Then add [Endless Whispers](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Endless Whispers) for the lulz.",
      "posted_by": "Ragamander",
      "html": "<div class=\"post evenItem\" id=\"PopularPost220712\" style=\"background-color: rgba(255,255,255,0.08);\">\n<span class=\"postContent\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl04_post\">@NARFNra: Simply put, the original <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Mirrorweave\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Mirrorweave\">Mirrorweave</a> (targeting <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Ink-Treader Nephilim\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Ink-Treader Nephilim\">Ink-Treader Nephilim</a>) is the last one to resolve, so everything will be a copy of the last creature targeted (because its copy will be the first to resolve).<br/><br/>@okfs87_7: If the last creature targeted is another <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Ink-Treader Nephilim\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Ink-Treader Nephilim\">Ink-Treader Nephilim</a>, it's not that big of a deal. Since only spells that are <i>cast</i> are copied by its ability, it won't further copy those copies. Otherwise, any single-target spell would cause an infinite loop with just a <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Clone\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Clone\">Clone</a>.<br/><br/>@ratrase &amp; OneFishTwoFish: <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Groundbreaker\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Groundbreaker\">Groundbreaker</a> is very similar to both <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Force of Savagery\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Force of Savagery\">Force of Savagery</a> and <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Ball Lightning\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Ball Lightning\">Ball Lightning</a>, and I'd wager that it's easier to generate <img align=\"absbottom\" alt=\"2\" src=\"/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&amp;name=2&amp;type=symbol\"/><img align=\"absbottom\" alt=\"White or Blue\" src=\"/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&amp;name=WU&amp;type=symbol\"/><img align=\"absbottom\" alt=\"White or Blue\" src=\"/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&amp;name=WU&amp;type=symbol\"/><img align=\"absbottom\" alt=\"Green\" src=\"/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&amp;name=G&amp;type=symbol\"/><img align=\"absbottom\" alt=\"Green\" src=\"/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&amp;name=G&amp;type=symbol\"/><img align=\"absbottom\" alt=\"Green\" src=\"/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&amp;name=G&amp;type=symbol\"/> than either <img align=\"absbottom\" alt=\"2\" src=\"/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&amp;name=2&amp;type=symbol\"/><img align=\"absbottom\" alt=\"White or Blue\" src=\"/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&amp;name=WU&amp;type=symbol\"/><img align=\"absbottom\" alt=\"White or Blue\" src=\"/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&amp;name=WU&amp;type=symbol\"/><img align=\"absbottom\" alt=\"Red\" src=\"/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&amp;name=R&amp;type=symbol\"/><img align=\"absbottom\" alt=\"Red\" src=\"/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&amp;name=R&amp;type=symbol\"/><img align=\"absbottom\" alt=\"Red\" src=\"/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&amp;name=R&amp;type=symbol\"/> or all the cards required to make the <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Force of Savagery\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Force of Savagery\">Force of Savagery</a> combo work. Then add <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Endless Whispers\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Endless Whispers\">Endless Whispers</a> for the lulz.</span>\n<div class=\"postDetails\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl04_postDetails\" style=\"padding-top: 5px;\">\n<div class=\"reportAbuse\">\n<a href=\"../../Classes/Controls/#\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl04_reportAbuseLink\" onclick=\"HandleReportPost(this, '220712'); return false;\">\r\n                                    Report Abuse</a>\u00a0\u00a0\r\n                                    \r\n                            </div>\n<div class=\"postedBy\">\r\n                                Posted By: \r\n                                <span id=\"PostedBy13722\">Ragamander</span>\r\n                                (1/16/2012 12:02:26 AM)\r\n                            </div>\n<div class=\"postRating\">\n<div class=\"postRatingLabel\">\r\n                                    Rating:\u00a0\r\n                                </div>\n<div style=\"float: left;\">\n<div class=\"starRating\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl04_postRating_starRating\"><img alt=\"0.5\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/LeftSolidSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"1.0\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/RightSolidSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"1.5\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/LeftSolidSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"2.0\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/RightSolidSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"2.5\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/LeftSolidSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"3.0\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/RightSolidSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"3.5\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/LeftSolidSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"4.0\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/RightSolidSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"4.5\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/LeftSolidSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"5.0\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/RightSolidSmall.png\"/>\n<br/>\n</div>\n</div>\n<br class=\"clear\"/>\n</div>\n<div class=\"postRating\">\n<div class=\"postRatingLabel\">\r\n                                    \u00a0\r\n                                </div>\n<div style=\"float: left;\">\n</div>\n<br class=\"clear\"/>\n</div>\n<br class=\"clear\"/>\n</div>\n</div>"
